                  <story-point caption='How Educated Are Women?' captured-sheet='qual 7' id='5' />
                  <story-point caption='Men on the Map: A Broader Educational Spread' captured-sheet='qual 8' id='6' />
                  <story-point caption='Contrasting Realities: Who’s Qualified and Who’s Left Behind?' captured-sheet='qual Dashboard 1' id='7'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <worksheet name='qual 10'>
                        <style delta-type='added'>
                          <style-rule element='axis'>
                            <encoding attr='space' class='0' field='[federated.0g21ci70msvqk71fwswgh09aualz].[Latitude (generated)]' field-type='quantitative' projection='EPSG:3857' scope='rows' type='space' />
                            <encoding attr='space' class='0' field='[federated.0g21ci70msvqk71fwswgh09aualz].[Longitude (generated)]' field-type='quantitative' projection='EPSG:3857' scope='cols' type='space' />
                          </style-rule>
                        </style>
                      </worksheet>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='21059' id='6' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='33273' x='9636' y='25294'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>From 2011 to 2021, Level 4+ qualifications increased by over 30%, while the population with no qualifications declined — signaling that formal education is becoming more common in an AI-driven world.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='12471' hidden='true' id='7' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='33273' x='9000' y='26000'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>By 2021, women outpaced men in Level 4+ qualifications, reflecting a shift in educational dominance that may influence future workforce leadership in AI-driven sectors.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='32353' hidden='true' id='8' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='33273' x='47364' y='26118'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Across regions, educational attainment varies drastically, with some areas reporting high levels of both degree holders and those with no qualifications — exposing deep educational inequality.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>In cities like Birmingham, nearly half the population holds a degree-level qualification while the other half has none — revealing stark educational polarization within the same region. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='27412' hidden='true' id='10' story-point-id='4' type-v2='text' w='20727' x='78455' y='38235'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Over the decade, women consistently increased their representation in higher qualification levels, especially at Level 4+, outpacing men and signaling a narrowing — or even reversal — of the gender education gap. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='8353' hidden='true' id='11' story-point-id='5' type-v2='text' w='82273' x='1727' y='90000'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Women are most concentrated in Level 4+ qualifications (30.77%) followed by those with no qualifications (21.96%) — a sign of both advancement and disparity within the female population.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='8706' hidden='true' id='12' story-point-id='6' type-v2='text' w='81727' x='2091' y='89529'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Men also show a high share of Level 4+ qualifications (30.4%), but with a noticeably higher presence in apprenticeships and fewer in the &quot;no qualifications&quot; category compared to women.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='24353' hidden='true' id='13' story-point-id='7' type-v2='text' w='16636' x='2273' y='25176'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#ffffff' fontsize='9'>Education Powerhouses: Regions with a high concentration of Level 4+ qualifications reflect stronger access to higher education and may correlate with local economic strength or university presence.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='24941' hidden='true' id='14' story-point-id='7' type-v2='text' w='18182' x='50818' y='24706'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#ffffff' fontsize='9'>Education Deserts: Areas shaded dark red reveal regions where a significant share of the population holds no formal qualifications, underscoring systemic barriers to education and socioeconomic challenges.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
